{"type":"message","id":"ae29c55e","parentId":"0c3c0f6c","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:22:02.081Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_eb26f34125914d088f6bef66","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/brave-search.md:3. Store the key in config or set `BRAVE_API_KEY` in the Gateway environment.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:summary: \"Date and time handling across envelopes, prompts, tools, and connectors\"\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:## Message envelopes (local by default)\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:This envelope timestamp is **host-local by default**, regardless of the provider timezone.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:      envelopeTimezone: \"local\", // \"utc\" | \"local\" | \"user\" | IANA timezone\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:      envelopeTimestamp: \"on\", // \"on\" | \"off\"\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:      envelopeElapsed: \"on\", // \"on\" | \"off\"\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:- `envelopeTimezone: \"utc\"` uses UTC.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:- `envelopeTimezone: \"local\"` uses the host timezone.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:- `envelopeTimezone: \"user\"` uses `agents.defaults.userTimezone` (falls back to host timezone).\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:- `envelopeTimestamp: \"off\"` removes absolute timestamps from envelope headers.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:- `envelopeElapsed: \"off\"` removes elapsed time suffixes (the `+2m` style).\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/date-time.md:same timezone selection as message envelopes (default: host-local).\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/logging.md:You can override both via the **`OPENCLAW_LOG_LEVEL`** environment variable (e.g. `OPENCLAW_LOG_LEVEL=debug`). The env var takes precedence over the config file, so you can raise verbosity for a single run without editing `openclaw.json`. You can also pass the global CLI option **`--log-level <level>`** (for example, `openclaw --log-level debug gateway run`), which overrides the environment variable for that command.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/perplexity.md:3. Store the key in config or set `PERPLEXITY_API_KEY` in the Gateway environment.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/perplexity.md:If you were already using OpenRouter for Perplexity Sonar, keep `provider: \"perplexity\"` and set `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` in the Gateway environment, or store an `sk-or-...` key in `tools.web.search.perplexity.apiKey`.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/perplexity.md:**Via environment:** set `PERPLEXITY_API_KEY` or `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/perplexity.md:in the Gateway process environment. For a gateway install, put it in\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/perplexity.md:`~/.openclaw/.env` (or your service environment). See [Env vars](/help/faq#how-does-openclaw-load-environment-variables).\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/perplexity.md:If `provider: \"perplexity\"` is configured and the Perplexity key SecretRef is unresolved with no env fallback, startup/reload fails fast."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/brave-search.md:3. Store the key in config or set `BRAVE_API_KEY` in the Gateway environment.\n/home/zhangyanbo/.npm-global/li